      <div class="entry">
        <h5><a href="/roomfordebate/2013/04/29/finding-solutions-for-syrias-growing-refugee-crisis">Solutions for Syria&#x27;s Refugees</a></h5>
        <p class="summary">The generosity of Syria’s neighbors is reaching its limit. What’s the best way to deal with the growing refugee crisis?  </p>
      </div>
      <div class="entry">
        <h5><a href="/roomfordebate/2012/12/05/recognizig-the-opposition-in-syria">Recognizing the Opposition in Syria</a></h5>
        <p class="summary">Should the U.S. officially recognize the opposition in Syria, or should Obama continue to use caution?  </p>
      </div>
      <div class="entry">
        <h5><a href="/roomfordebate/2012/08/08/how-to-end-the-war-in-syria">How to End the Chaos in Syria</a></h5>
        <p class="summary">Syria is descending toward civil war, if it is not already embroiled in one. What can be done to stop this, or at least limit it? </p>
      </div>
